<td><i>PitRuS</i></td>
<td>simple stem with t-infix after first radical, indicating reciprocal or reflexive</td>
<td>Arabic stem VIII (<i>ifta‚Äòala</i>) and Aramaic <i>‚Äôithpe‚Äòal</i> (tG)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>II.2</td>
<td>Dt</td>
<td><i>PutaRRuS</i></td>
<td>doubled second radical preceded by infixed t, indicating intensive reflexive</td>
<td>Arabic stem V (<i>tafa‚Äò‚Äòala</i>) and Hebrew <i>hithpa‚Äòel</i> (tD)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>III.2</td>
<td>≈†t</td>
<td><i>≈°utaPRuS</i></td>
<td>≈°-preformative with t-infix, indicating reflexive causative</td>
<td>Arabic stem X (<i>istaf‚Äòala</i>) and Aramaic <i>‚Äôittaph‚Äòal</i> (tC)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>IV.2</td>
<td>Nt</td>
<td><i>itaPRuS</i></td>
<td>n-preformative with a t-infix preceding the first radical, indicating reflexive passive</td>
<td rowspan="6" bgcolor="gray"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I.3</td>
